&lt;p&gt;I made a benchmark to test the performance of each solution that don&apos;t use external libraries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jsben.ch/ZQyZo&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;JSBen.ch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;reduce()&lt;/code&gt; option, posted by @Nina Scholz seems to be the optimal one.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/tc39/proposal-array-grouping&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noreferrer&quot;&gt;A proposal&lt;/a&gt; that adds &lt;code&gt;Array.prototype.groupBy&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;Array.prototype.groupByToMap&lt;/code&gt; is now on Stage 3!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When it reaches Stage 4 and is implemented on most major browsers, you&apos;ll be able to do this:&lt;/p&gt;
